my Vladimir Grigorevich?

747
00:55:12,213 --> 00:55:15,882
My wife's heart on a platter?
Her kidneys, with salt?

748
00:55:15,883 --> 00:55:18,675
But of course, my dear Chertkov.
Whatever pleases you.

749
00:55:18,677 --> 00:55:19,969
The china, the estate,

750
00:55:19,970 --> 00:55:22,556
permanent copyright
on anything I've ever written?

751
00:55:22,557 --> 00:55:25,976
Oh, anything for you,
my love."

752
00:55:31,691 --> 00:55:33,356
Give that to me.
No.

753
00:55:33,358 --> 00:55:36,027
Give it to me, you little weasel!
Sofya!

754
00:55:36,028 --> 00:55:38,572
Give it to me! Give it to me!
Sofya.

755
00:55:39,197 --> 00:55:40,447
Now...
Can I have...?

756
00:55:40,447 --> 00:55:42,865
Can I not have some...?

757
00:55:42,867 --> 00:55:47,579
Can I not have some...?
You'll kill him, Mama.

758
00:55:47,581 --> 00:55:51,876
Well, that's what you want,
isn't it? You want him to die!

759
00:55:51,878 --> 00:55:53,836
Lev.

760
00:55:56,506 --> 00:56:00,177
It's all right, it's all right.
Let's get him out of here.

761
00:56:08,102 --> 00:56:10,769
You don't deceive me
for one moment.

762
00:56:10,771 --> 00:56:14,358
I know exactly
what you're doing.

763
00:56:17,985 --> 00:56:20,322
I want to see the will.

764
00:56:20,780 --> 00:56:24,701
It is my right as his wife
in the sight of God.

765
00:56:24,702 --> 00:56:26,994
What are you afraid of?

766
00:56:26,996 --> 00:56:29,039
You.

767
00:56:29,081 --> 00:56:31,081
I'm afraid of you.

768
00:56:33,043 --> 00:56:34,835
The press are
bloodthirsty, Sofya.

769
00:56:34,836 --> 00:56:38,047
Had I wished,
I could have demolished you.

770
00:56:38,048 --> 00:56:39,257
You make it easy.

771
00:56:39,258 --> 00:56:41,800
Then tell them anything
you want. Go ahead. Ruin us!

772
00:56:41,802 --> 00:56:45,221
I have too much respect
for Lev Nikolayevich!

773
00:56:45,222 --> 00:56:46,597
You're lucky!

774
00:56:46,599 --> 00:56:49,182
Why can't my husband
see you for what you are?

775
00:56:49,184 --> 00:56:54,438
If I had a wife like you,
I would've blown my brains out!

776
00:56:54,439 --> 00:56:57,735
Or gone to America.

777
00:57:40,985 --> 00:57:43,278
I hope you're feeling better.

778
00:57:43,280 --> 00:57:44,822
Mm.

779
00:57:48,410 --> 00:57:50,871
Do you like the opera?

780
00:57:50,954 --> 00:57:52,914
Yes.

781
00:57:57,836 --> 00:58:01,840
I'm very sorry
about everything.

782
00:58:07,177 --> 00:58:10,224
This aria is so beautiful.

783
00:58:10,599 --> 00:58:14,684
It's about a woman who's been abandoned
by the man she loves.

784
00:58:14,686 --> 00:58:17,648
Everyone finds that
very moving...

785
00:58:18,316 --> 00:58:20,608
in the opera.

786
00:58:31,537 --> 00:58:35,164
Our life together
has become intolerable.

787
00:58:35,331 --> 00:58:36,875
Sit down, Valentin.

788
00:58:36,876 --> 00:58:38,250
Really, I'm expected
at Telyatinki.

789
00:58:38,251 --> 00:58:40,211
No, no, no, please.
Come, enjoy your dinner.

790
00:58:40,213 --> 00:58:44,298
We've just had a disagreement,
like all married couples.

791
00:58:44,717 --> 00:58:48,510
Despite good cause for it,
I have never stopped loving you.

792
00:58:48,512 --> 00:58:50,387
Of course.

793
00:58:50,389 --> 00:58:52,306
But God knows
you don't make it easy.

794
00:58:52,307 --> 00:58:53,516
Why should it be easy?

795
00:58:53,517 --> 00:58:55,934
I am the work of your life,
you're the work of mine.

796
00:58:55,936 --> 00:58:58,689
That's what love is.

797
00:58:59,273 --> 00:59:01,150
I should go.
No, sit down.

798
00:59:02,276 --> 00:59:07,238
Oh, so that's what love is?
Eh?

799
00:59:07,365 --> 00:59:08,572
Does that surprise you, boy?

800
00:59:08,572 --> 00:59:10,534
I thought it might be
a touch quieter, but...

801
00:59:11,452 --> 00:59:12,952
God bless you.
Bless you.

802
00:59:12,954 --> 00:59:15,539
He's right, though.

803
00:59:16,081 --> 00:59:19,333
If we can't live a decent, quiet life,

804
00:59:19,334 --> 00:59:24,130
if I can't work and find some
peace, then I shall go away.

805
00:59:24,131 --> 00:59:27,592
Go?
Not to Chertkov, but I shall go.

806
00:59:27,593 --> 00:59:31,305
Go where?
Dushan says you're killing me!

807
00:59:32,847 --> 00:59:35,642
Then go!
Go anywhere you please!

808
00:59:36,352 --> 00:59:39,271
Go anywhere you please!

809
00:59:39,564 --> 00:59:42,273
I hate you!

810
00:59:43,108 --> 00:59:45,068
I hate what you've become!

811
00:59:45,570 --> 00:59:48,320
Countess.
Go. No.

812
00:59:48,322 --> 00:59:49,865
Dushan!

813
00:59:50,447 --> 00:59:53,827
Oh, God.
Countess?

814
00:59:53,827 --> 00:59:56,746
Countess! Is she all right?

815
00:59:56,747 --> 00:59:58,289
Is she all right?

816
00:59:58,291 --> 01:00:02,960
Sofya. Sofya, are you all right?
Open your eyes.

817
01:00:02,961 --> 01:00:04,671
Open your eyes.

818
01:00:05,798 --> 01:00:08,048
Oh! Oh, my back!

819
01:00:08,050 --> 01:00:09,802
Oh, my... Oh!

820
01:00:09,802 --> 01:00:11,552
Oh, my back.

821
01:00:12,470 --> 01:00:14,639
You're lying on a fork.

822
01:00:17,142 --> 01:00:20,061
Sit up and you'll
improve markedly.

823
01:00:20,271 --> 01:00:22,980
If you'll be good enough
to take her upstairs.

824
01:00:22,981 --> 01:00:26,110
Come along, countess,
come with me.

825
01:00:45,588 --> 01:00:47,296
Masha.

826
01:00:59,852 --> 01:01:01,769
I'm sorry.

827
01:01:04,231 --> 01:01:06,023
It was terrible there today.

828
01:01:06,983 --> 01:01:10,818
They loved each other so much,
I'm sure of it, I'm sure they do,

829
01:01:10,820 --> 01:01:14,532
but you see what it becomes,
and you just wish that you could...

830
01:01:18,662 --> 01:01:20,831
Is something
the matter?

831
01:01:21,039 --> 01:01:22,916
Masha?

832
01:01:25,418 --> 01:01:29,088
I'm... I'm going back
to Moscow.

833
01:01:29,381 --> 01:01:30,548
What?

834
01:01:30,550 --> 01:01:33,884
Chertkov spoke with me
this afternoon.

835
01:01:33,885 --> 01:01:37,054
He said I could
be more useful there.

836
01:01:37,055 --> 01:01:39,266
Which means...
Means he's punishing us.

837
01:01:39,267 --> 01:01:41,893
He's punishing me.

838
01:01:41,894 --> 01:01:44,728
He's punishing me for befriending
Sofya Andreyevna.

839
01:01:44,729 --> 01:01:46,021
This is Chertkov.

840
01:01:46,023 --> 01:01:48,231
We've both disappointed him,
but I don't care.

841
01:01:48,233 --> 01:01:50,402
I don't care either,
but you can't leave.

842
01:01:50,403 --> 01:01:53,528
I'm going to talk to him. I'm going to
make him make you stay.

843
01:01:53,530 --> 01:01:57,409
No. I want to go.
Yes. What?

844
01:01:57,577 --> 01:02:00,079
I'm leaving the movement.

845
01:02:05,543 --> 01:02:08,043
Sit down, sit down.

846
01:02:09,130 --> 01:02:11,088
You can't leave Tolstoy.
I'm not.

847
01:02:11,090 --> 01:02:14,008
You can't leave.
No, I'm not.

848
01:02:15,177 --> 01:02:17,596
When I read his confession,
it moved me, Valya.

849
01:02:17,597 --> 01:02:18,804
Yes.

850
01:02:18,805 --> 01:02:21,097
When he was searching
for freedom.

851
01:02:21,099 --> 01:02:24,434
Freedom from anger,
freedom from attachment,

852
01:02:24,436 --> 01:02:28,188
freedom from all the superstition
and the nonsense of the Church.

853
01:02:28,189 --> 01:02:31,358
I mean, it moved me
so much.

854
01:02:31,360 --> 01:02:33,903
And that's what I thought
it would be about.

855
01:02:33,905 --> 01:02:36,447
I mean, isn't that
what it's about?

856
01:02:36,447 --> 01:02:39,075
Freedom and love?

857
01:02:40,912 --> 01:02:43,914
They mix it all up.

858
01:02:49,293 --> 01:02:51,505
Come with me.

859
01:02:53,798 --> 01:02:55,758
Please?

860
01:03:10,316 --> 01:03:11,858
I can't.

861
01:03:22,662 --> 01:03:26,497
I'm going to my room.
Wait.

862
01:03:27,499 --> 01:03:29,459
Masha.

863
01:03:37,260 --> 01:03:40,845
Masha, please. I can't.

864
01:03:41,180 --> 01:03:43,097
I need you.

865
01:03:48,144 --> 01:03:50,189
I know you do.

866
01:03:52,023 --> 01:03:54,485
I know.

867
01:04:06,037 --> 01:04:09,874
A-Y. A-Y.

868
01:04:10,668 --> 01:04:13,378
A-Y.

869
01:04:14,881 --> 01:04:17,800
What was it?
I don't remember.

870
01:04:18,633 --> 01:04:22,721
Was it your...?
No, no, no.

871
01:04:22,722 --> 01:04:25,432
You rest now.

872
01:04:26,474 --> 01:04:28,519
You rest.

873
01:05:02,845 --> 01:05:05,514
Is everything in order?

874
01:05:21,363 --> 01:05:23,405
Good afternoon,
Lev Nikolayevich.

875
01:05:23,407 --> 01:05:25,242
Is it?

876
01:05:40,298 --> 01:05:43,259
Remember that this will ensure

877
01:05:43,260 --> 01:05:46,135
that your complete works
will live in the public domain.

878
01:05:46,137 --> 01:05:47,806
Monumentous.

879
01:05:47,807 --> 01:05:52,018
Your works are the birthright
of the Russian people.

880
01:05:52,019 --> 01:05:56,773
And now they will
possess them forever.

881
01:05:58,276 --> 01:06:00,235
Yes?

882
01:06:00,485 --> 01:06:02,653
I need a pen.

883
01:06:02,655 --> 01:06:05,990
Oh. Of course, of course.

884
01:06:06,617 --> 01:06:09,244
I, uh...
What?

885
01:06:13,499 --> 01:06:15,125
I don't seem
to have a pen.

886
01:06:15,126 --> 01:06:17,543
You're a secretary.
How can you not have a pen?

887
01:06:17,543 --> 01:06:20,798
He's a secretary too.
Ask him.

888
01:06:21,090 --> 01:06:24,384
Valentin Fedorovich,
do you have a pen?

889
01:06:24,385 --> 01:06:26,387
I...

890
01:06:34,269 --> 01:06:36,188
Yes.

891
01:06:36,856 --> 01:06:39,273
Yes, I have a pen.

892
01:06:53,372 --> 01:06:55,624
Are you all right?

893
01:06:57,168 --> 01:06:59,168
I'm a conspirator.

894
01:06:59,543 --> 01:07:01,255
Nothing more.

895
01:07:35,581 --> 01:07:37,914
Lev Nikolayevich.

896
01:07:37,916 --> 01:07:40,960
May I ask you a question that has nothing
to do with the work?

897
01:07:40,961 --> 01:07:42,921
Of course, my dear.

898
01:07:43,421 --> 01:07:46,090
Do you love your wife?

899
01:07:48,260 --> 01:07:50,844
You see, when I was
courting Sofya,

900
01:07:50,845 --> 01:07:54,639
she was so young
and so pure

901
01:07:54,849 --> 01:07:58,353
it just seemed impossible
that I could ever have her.

902
01:07:58,354 --> 01:08:02,106
I didn't want to tell her
how I felt, and yet...

903
01:08:02,108 --> 01:08:05,277
I wanted to tell her
nothing else.

904
01:08:05,278 --> 01:08:07,278
So I wrote down
a string of letters

905
01:08:07,280 --> 01:08:10,030
and asked her
if she would decipher them.

906
01:08:10,032 --> 01:08:14,242
At first, she was completely
confused and thought it was
some sort of game or something.

907
01:08:14,244 --> 01:08:16,829
So I gave her a clue.
One clue.

908
01:08:17,289 --> 01:08:22,126
"The first two Y's," I said,
"stand for 'your youth,"'

909
01:08:22,127 --> 01:08:24,086
and that was all I said.

910
01:08:24,087 --> 01:08:25,670
And then...

911
01:08:26,088 --> 01:08:29,217
the most miraculous thing
happened.

912
01:08:29,676 --> 01:08:32,929
She simply spoke
the phrase:

913
01:08:33,637 --> 01:08:38,057
"Your youth and your desire
for happiness

914
01:08:38,058 --> 01:08:40,728
cruelly remind me of my age

915
01:08:40,728 --> 01:08:44,774
and the impossibility
of happiness for me."

916
01:08:45,609 --> 01:08:48,652
The entire phrase, my phrase.

917
01:08:48,777 --> 01:08:51,780
As if she'd read my mind.

918
01:08:52,824 --> 01:08:56,828
In that moment, we both knew
we would always be together.

919
01:08:57,494 --> 01:09:00,914
And for the first few years,
we were

920
01:09:00,915 --> 01:09:03,083
incredibly,

921
01:09:03,085 --> 01:09:05,670
terrifyingly...

922
01:09:07,838 --> 01:09:09,841
happy.

923
01:09:16,932 --> 01:09:19,475
And now this.

924
01:09:36,661 --> 01:09:38,411
I'm leaving Telyatinki.

925
01:09:38,828 --> 01:09:40,037
Really?

926
01:09:40,038 --> 01:09:42,623
Yes. I'm going to Moscow.

927
01:09:42,790 --> 01:09:45,042
She's leading you around
by the nose, my boy.

928
01:09:45,043 --> 01:09:48,503
Look, you say that
the movement is about love.

929
01:09:48,504 --> 01:09:51,715
And it is. The love
that he teaches us.

930
01:09:51,716 --> 01:09:54,677
The love that binds
all mankind together.

931
01:09:54,679 --> 01:09:56,679
I've never met mankind.

932
01:09:56,679 --> 01:10:00,557
I've only ever met men or women.
Imperfect men, imperfect women.

933
01:10:00,558 --> 01:10:03,310
Yes. But Lev Nikolayevich
also teaches us

934
01:10:03,311 --> 01:10:08,149
that love cannot be weak-minded.
It cannot be stupid.

935
01:10:11,570 --> 01:10:15,239
Go. We will miss you.

936
01:10:16,156 --> 01:10:19,201
Our naive sentimentalist.

937
01:10:20,829 --> 01:10:23,205
Keep clear.

938
01:10:24,540 --> 01:10:26,960
BO Y:
Give it to me.

939
01:10:35,094 --> 01:10:37,637
Leovochka?
Hm?

940
01:10:43,393 --> 01:10:47,354
Kashnikov wants to buy the rights to
your work after your death.

941
01:10:47,355 --> 01:10:49,940
Oh, then I shall try and die
as soon as is convenient.

942
01:10:49,942 --> 01:10:52,318
Oh, come on, don't be silly.
Come, look.

943
01:10:52,319 --> 01:10:56,739
Look, he has offered
1 million rubles.

944
01:10:58,199 --> 01:11:00,242
How can you not be pleased?

945
01:11:00,243 --> 01:11:02,286
I don't write for publishers,
I write for people.

946
01:11:02,286 --> 01:11:03,703
Well, where are
you going?

947
01:11:03,704 --> 01:11:06,664
Valentin is in the library.
He wants to see me.

948
01:11:06,665 --> 01:11:10,795
Fine! Fine, go ahead and let your
wretched family starve.

949
01:11:10,878 --> 01:11:14,256
I don't see anyone starving
in this house.

950
01:11:14,257 --> 01:11:16,091
On the contrary,

951
01:11:16,092 --> 01:11:18,844
our privilege revolts me.

952
01:11:18,844 --> 01:11:21,097
Well, you're the first
to the trough!

953
01:11:22,973 --> 01:11:25,476
Always have been.

954
01:12:04,014 --> 01:12:06,809
Now, what is it, my boy?

955
01:12:06,810 --> 01:12:09,228
You look unhappy.

956
01:12:10,187 --> 01:12:12,690
What do you
want to tell me?

957
01:12:22,284 --> 01:12:24,326
Sofya!

958
01:12:24,536 --> 01:12:26,661
Sofya!

959
01:12:31,460 --> 01:12:33,835
What are you doing?

960
01:12:33,962 --> 01:12:37,589
How could you
do this to me?

961
01:12:38,048 --> 01:12:39,382
You're not well.

962
01:12:39,384 --> 01:12:43,596
You... You just hurt me
again and again.

963
01:12:43,597 --> 01:12:47,893
You tear pieces off me
until there's nothing left.

964
01:12:49,393 --> 01:12:52,896
I don't know who I am anymore.

965
01:12:55,734 --> 01:12:58,652
I read your diary.

966
01:12:59,320 --> 01:13:01,989
I know what
you've done.

967
01:13:02,615 --> 01:13:04,951
You behave like this,
I have no choice.

968
01:13:06,869 --> 01:13:08,537
Now give me the gun.
No!

969
01:13:08,538 --> 01:13:11,625
Please, countess.
Give me the gun, please.

970
01:13:56,002 --> 01:13:59,088
I'd like you to
stay here tonight.

971
01:14:01,634 --> 01:14:03,134
Yes, of course.

972
01:14:27,659 --> 01:14:28,909
Valentin.

973
01:14:28,911 --> 01:14:30,202
Get up.
What?

974
01:14:30,203 --> 01:14:32,454
He's leaving.

975
01:14:36,167 --> 01:14:38,460
Shh!

976
01:14:42,841 --> 01:14:46,009
Pack essentials only.

977
01:14:46,177 --> 01:14:49,762
Nothing that isn't
absolutely necessary.

978
01:14:49,763 --> 01:14:51,515
Please, we must hurry.

979
01:14:51,516 --> 01:14:53,391
Where will you go?
Your coat, Papa.

980
01:14:53,393 --> 01:14:55,101
We don't need a plan,
we just go.

981
01:14:55,103 --> 01:14:58,230
A lantern, I think.
It's very dark tonight.

982
01:14:58,231 --> 01:15:01,484
And the apparatus
for giving an enema.

983
01:15:09,451 --> 01:15:11,911
Everything's ready.

984
01:15:16,958 --> 01:15:19,210
Dushan, you all right?

985
01:15:19,210 --> 01:15:20,877
Please, go steady.

986
01:15:20,878 --> 01:15:22,587
You all right?

987
01:15:22,588 --> 01:15:24,548
Papa?

988
01:15:27,886 --> 01:15:29,886
He's changed
his mind.

989
01:15:29,887 --> 01:15:32,264
He's going back
to the house.

990
01:16:03,504 --> 01:16:06,382
Do you want
to go back?

991
01:16:08,009 --> 01:16:10,094
No.

992
01:16:11,304 --> 01:16:15,768
This life is behind me now.

993
01:16:30,865 --> 01:16:33,451
Help me up.
Yes, of course.

994
01:16:43,128 --> 01:16:45,296
Give this to Sofya.

995
01:16:45,297 --> 01:16:47,423
Yes.

996
01:16:52,262 --> 01:16:55,263
Be well, be well.

997
01:17:03,899 --> 01:17:07,025
Don't cry, don't cry.

998
01:17:07,027 --> 01:17:09,570
I'll send for you when I can.

999
01:17:22,375 --> 01:17:24,627
Drive on.

1000
01:17:47,942 --> 01:17:50,237
He's gone.

1001
01:17:50,820 --> 01:17:53,780
For good?
I think so, yes.

1002
01:17:55,909 --> 01:17:59,369
Oh, Sasha, darling, I know you know
where your father is.

1003
01:17:59,370 --> 01:18:02,539
So, darling, please,
this is not a time to
play games, please?

1004
01:18:02,540 --> 01:18:07,335
Countess, I have this for you.

1005
01:18:15,887 --> 01:18:21,141
<i>My position in the house
has become intolerable.</i>

1006
01:18:21,143 --> 01:18:26,188
<i>What I'm doing now is what
people have commonly done,</i>

1007
01:18:26,313 --> 01:18:28,399
<i>leave their worldly life behind</i>

1008
01:18:28,400 --> 01:18:33,780
<i>to spend their last days
in peace and solitude.</i>

1009
01:18:38,786 --> 01:18:41,454
The pond.

1010
01:18:42,496 --> 01:18:44,707
Mama!
Countess!

1011
01:18:44,708 --> 01:18:45,916
Please, Mama!

1012
01:18:45,917 --> 01:18:48,752
<i>Please understand this
and don't come after me,</i>

1013
01:18:48,753 --> 01:18:51,505
<i>even if you find out where I am.</i>

1014
01:18:51,505 --> 01:18:54,382
<i>Your coming would only
make our position worse</i>

1015
01:18:54,384 --> 01:18:56,760
<i>and would not alter my decision.</i>

1016
01:18:56,761 --> 01:18:59,137
Mother!

1017
01:19:00,264 --> 01:19:04,226
<i>I beg you to forgive me
for everything I've done to you,</i>

1018
01:19:04,228 --> 01:19:07,230
<i>just as I forgive you
with all my soul</i>

1019
01:19:07,563 --> 01:19:10,525
<i>for everything you've done to me.</i>

1020
01:19:18,826 --> 01:19:20,451
Countess!

1021
01:19:26,333 --> 01:19:28,585
Mama!

1022
01:19:29,545 --> 01:19:31,670
Mama!

1023
01:19:32,880 --> 01:19:36,217
Mama!
I have her!

1024
01:19:38,554 --> 01:19:44,350
Here! Here! Take her! Take her.
Mama!

1025
01:19:48,812 --> 01:19:53,442
Ivan, Ivan, go to the house.
Get a doctor, quickly, quickly!

1026
01:19:53,735 --> 01:19:57,446
Turn her.
Turn her over, come on.

1027
01:20:02,244 --> 01:20:04,911
Oh, God. Thank God.

1028
01:20:19,761 --> 01:20:24,766
Ivan, go to the station.
Find out which train he took.

1029
01:20:24,932 --> 01:20:26,851
For God's sake.

1030
01:20:27,393 --> 01:20:30,520
Come, come, come.
Let's get you to bed.

1031
01:20:30,521 --> 01:20:34,232
Ready and up. There we...
Let's go, there.

1032
01:20:37,654 --> 01:20:39,905
Thank you.

1033
01:21:01,386 --> 01:21:04,763
Here, tea.

1034
01:21:05,432 --> 01:21:07,850
She's exhausted
herself.

1035
01:21:07,851 --> 01:21:10,185
She slept for
nearly four hours.

1036
01:21:10,186 --> 01:21:14,355
Well, I'm glad she can sleep.
The pain subsides a little.

1037
01:21:14,356 --> 01:21:17,652
The noise subsides
a little.

1038
01:21:20,989 --> 01:21:23,031
Come in.

1039
01:21:23,408 --> 01:21:26,576
A message, miss.
For me?

1040
01:21:26,869 --> 01:21:28,663
From your father.

1041
01:21:31,333 --> 01:21:35,961
<i>My darling Sasha, I have stopped
to rest at Shamardino.</i>

1042
01:21:35,962 --> 01:21:39,047
<i>I'll wait for you to join me here.</i>

1043
01:21:39,048 --> 01:21:42,676
<i>Please ask Valentin to stay
and look after your mother.</i>

1044
01:21:42,677 --> 01:21:47,222
<i>When you arrive, we'll continue
the journey south together.</i>

1045
01:21:47,223 --> 01:21:48,975
<i>Your loving father.</i>

1046
01:22:04,990 --> 01:22:07,243
They've all gone.

1047
01:22:07,701 --> 01:22:09,870
I'm here.

1048
01:22:12,289 --> 01:22:14,166
Oh...

1049
01:22:14,167 --> 01:22:18,671
You're writing to your girl.
Oh, how lovely.

1050
01:22:18,672 --> 01:22:21,465
I'm not sure she is my girl.

1051
01:22:21,466 --> 01:22:23,717
But you believe
you'll see her again.

1052
01:22:23,719 --> 01:22:26,011
I very much hope so.
Yes.

1053
01:22:26,012 --> 01:22:27,929
Yes.

1054
01:22:28,807 --> 01:22:32,310
I know you know
where he is, Valentin.

1055
01:22:33,353 --> 01:22:38,148
Sofya Andreyevna...
I won't ask you to betray his trust.

1056
01:22:38,149 --> 01:22:41,735
I just need you
to go to him. I do.

1057
01:22:41,737 --> 01:22:44,738
I have to see him.
I have to talk to him.

1058
01:22:44,739 --> 01:22:48,951
I won't make a scene.
You can promise him that. I...

1059
01:22:50,786 --> 01:22:53,539
I just want to see him.

1060
01:23:04,634 --> 01:23:08,721
"Tolstoy abandons home,
whereabouts unknown."

1061
01:23:08,722 --> 01:23:12,056
"The sage of Yasnaya Polyana
takes flight."

1062
01:23:12,057 --> 01:23:14,518
That's Tolstoy.

1063
01:23:15,020 --> 01:23:18,146
I hope it's not
too much for him.

1064
01:23:25,696 --> 01:23:27,655
Ah... Where are we?

1065
01:23:27,656 --> 01:23:29,741
It's all right.
Everything's fine.

1066
01:23:30,994 --> 01:23:33,870
Shh, shh, shh.
Let me take your temperature.

1067
01:23:36,081 --> 01:23:38,210
Come on.

1068
01:24:06,404 --> 01:24:09,197
Be mindful of these steps.

1069
01:24:21,962 --> 01:24:25,213
We've come
to the end of the world.

1070
01:24:47,612 --> 01:24:49,445
This is the stationmaster.

1071
01:24:49,446 --> 01:24:52,324
He's very kind. He said we may have
his home for as long as we want it.

1072
01:24:52,326 --> 01:24:55,118
There are no inns nearby,
so we are lucky.

1073
01:24:55,119 --> 01:24:57,453
Yes, very lucky.
Yes.

1074
01:24:57,454 --> 01:24:59,707
You'll be comfortable
here, Papa.

1075
01:24:59,708 --> 01:25:03,793
The rest of us, we'll find cots,
or sleep in the station.

1076
01:25:03,795 --> 01:25:05,296
And then we'll be on our way.

1077
01:25:05,297 --> 01:25:09,759
Yes. Yes, Papa.
We'll be on our way.

1078
01:25:16,516 --> 01:25:18,058
Excuse me?

1079
01:25:19,518 --> 01:25:21,771
I'd like to send
a telegram, please.

1080
01:25:22,646 --> 01:25:24,315
Uh...

1081
01:25:24,317 --> 01:25:26,567
At Astapovo. Stop.

1082
01:25:27,652 --> 01:25:30,987
Tolstoy ill. Stop.

1083
01:25:31,697 --> 01:25:33,240
Temperature high.

1084
01:25:33,616 --> 01:25:37,661
<i>You can send it to Countess Sofya
Andreyevna Tolstoya,</i>

1085
01:25:37,661 --> 01:25:40,748
<i>Yasnaya Polyana, Tula Province.</i>

1086
01:25:40,750 --> 01:25:44,835
Please come back.
Please come back.

1087
01:25:56,097 --> 01:25:59,141
Concern for Lev Nikolayevich's
health has been expressed

1088
01:25:59,143 --> 01:26:02,269
by people as diverse as
Mr. Henry James

1089
01:26:02,270 --> 01:26:04,355
and Mr. Joseph Conrad.

1090
01:26:04,356 --> 01:26:08,317
Lev Nikolayevich's temperature currently
stands at 40 degrees Celsius.

1091
01:26:08,317 --> 01:26:10,485
That is 104 degrees
Fahrenheit.

1092
01:26:10,487 --> 01:26:13,948
His blood pressure, which is hypertonic,
is 180 over 100.

1093
01:26:13,949 --> 01:26:15,908
However, it should be added,

1094
01:26:15,909 --> 01:26:18,202
Lev Nikolayevich's manner

1095
01:26:18,203 --> 01:26:19,994
and mental acuity
Bulgakov!

1096
01:26:19,995 --> 01:26:22,373
is as great as ever.

1097
01:26:22,875 --> 01:26:24,875
Where is he? Take me to him.
This way.

1098
01:26:24,875 --> 01:26:27,670
He left. It's astonishing.
He actually finally left.

1099
01:26:27,670 --> 01:26:32,174
He was very sick, too sick to travel.
It's a triumph for the movement.

1100
01:26:42,893 --> 01:26:45,480
He looks so small.

1101
01:26:46,021 --> 01:26:48,149
Papa.

1102
01:26:49,652 --> 01:26:52,195
Oh, it's you.

1103
01:26:52,404 --> 01:26:55,530
My dear friend,

1104
01:26:55,531 --> 01:26:57,783
what is all of this?

1105
01:26:57,784 --> 01:27:01,411
Well, I needed
to see you.

1106
01:27:02,289 --> 01:27:04,039
Thank you.

1107
01:27:05,125 --> 01:27:07,835
We have so much to do.

1108
01:27:09,378 --> 01:27:12,255
Have you seen Sofya?

1109
01:27:12,423 --> 01:27:15,009
I've made a point not to.

1110
01:27:15,176 --> 01:27:17,052
She'll come.

1111
01:27:17,054 --> 01:27:20,597
I don't know when she'll come,
but she'll come. I know that.

1112
01:27:20,598 --> 01:27:23,976
And we'll be ready.
Ready for what?

1113
01:27:27,105 --> 01:27:29,899
I'm sorry, but I'm afraid
it's time for your enema.

1114
01:27:29,900 --> 01:27:31,942
Don't apologize,
my friend.

1115
01:27:31,942 --> 01:27:34,945
Your enemas have become the
news of the world.

1116
01:28:27,831 --> 01:28:31,460
My only concern is getting
the copy back to London in time.

1117
01:28:31,460 --> 01:28:33,503
Good morning, gentlemen.

1118
01:28:37,174 --> 01:28:39,592
I'm sure you will all be
as relieved as I am

1119
01:28:39,594 --> 01:28:44,598
that Lev Nikolayevich slept
a relatively peaceful night.

1120
01:28:44,891 --> 01:28:48,601
His temperature remains
40 degrees Celsius.

1121
01:28:48,603 --> 01:28:50,980
And his blood pressure
is also hypertonic.

1122
01:28:50,981 --> 01:28:53,356
That having been said, however,

1123
01:28:53,357 --> 01:28:57,194
his mind remains agile
and full of fortitude.

1124
01:28:57,195 --> 01:28:59,904
It's the countess.
Of course, we have to remember...

1125
01:28:59,905 --> 01:29:01,739
Is she here?
It's the countess.

1126
01:29:01,740 --> 01:29:04,243
Let's see.
Where is she?

1127
01:29:04,244 --> 01:29:07,829
It's the countess!
Which car is it?

1128
01:29:26,391 --> 01:29:29,268
The Countess!
There she is.

1129
01:29:29,728 --> 01:29:31,937
Countess Sofya.

1130
01:29:33,272 --> 01:29:34,731
She's coming this way.

1131
01:29:34,732 --> 01:29:38,444
Not before she stops to tell them lies,
catalog my atrocities.

1132
01:29:38,445 --> 01:29:40,904
Let me talk to her.

1133
01:29:40,905 --> 01:29:42,990
I want to see my husband.

1134
01:29:43,158 --> 01:29:44,574
Yes.

1135
01:29:44,576 --> 01:29:46,244
I'll, um...

1136
01:29:46,453 --> 01:29:48,703
I want to see him now!

1137
01:29:48,704 --> 01:29:50,830
Countess! Countess!

1138
01:29:50,831 --> 01:29:53,833
Oh, Valentin.
I want to see him, please.

1139
01:29:53,835 --> 01:29:56,086
I'm not sure now
is the right time, countess.

1140
01:29:56,087 --> 01:29:58,756
Yes, it is.
It's the right time for me.

1141
01:29:58,757 --> 01:30:01,174
Have you had any contact?

1142
01:30:02,302 --> 01:30:05,386
It might be a better idea, countess,
I really think, if you just waited...

1143
01:30:05,387 --> 01:30:06,846
He only left because of you.

1144
01:30:06,847 --> 01:30:08,725
Countess!

1145
01:30:16,106 --> 01:30:17,565
I want to see my husband.

1146
01:30:17,567 --> 01:30:19,818
He's too weak
to see you now, Mother.

1147
01:30:19,819 --> 01:30:22,946
He's not too weak to see you.
Not too weak to see that... Pfft.

1148
01:30:22,947 --> 01:30:25,574
Do you really want
to do this here?

1149
01:30:25,576 --> 01:30:30,328
So I am the leper outside the gate, while
he sleeps with the devil himself.

1150
01:30:30,329 --> 01:30:34,542
Chertkov is here because Father
asked him to be here.

1151
01:30:35,627 --> 01:30:39,504
Is that true?
Yes.

1152
01:30:42,259 --> 01:30:46,262
Well, did you tell him that
I nearly drowned in the pond?

1153
01:30:46,512 --> 01:30:49,681
We didn't need to.
It's been in all the papers.

1154
01:30:49,682 --> 01:30:52,393
Please, let me take you back.
What did he say?

1155
01:30:53,311 --> 01:30:57,106
He said that if you killed
yourself, he'd be upset.

1156
01:30:58,275 --> 01:31:02,987
He'd be upset?
Horribly upset.

1157
01:31:03,362 --> 01:31:05,823
But he could not have
acted other than he did.

1158
01:31:05,824 --> 01:31:07,991
I want to see him.

1159
01:31:09,578 --> 01:31:12,162
He's my husband.
He's not your husband.

1160
01:31:12,163 --> 01:31:13,454
Oh, you're unbearable.

1161
01:31:13,455 --> 01:31:17,085
And you are a stone-hearted
bitch of a daughter.

1162
01:31:19,253 --> 01:31:20,753
I lost five children!

1163
01:31:20,754 --> 01:31:23,298
Why couldn't one of them
have been you?

1164
01:31:24,719 --> 01:31:27,179
Did she just say that?

1165
01:31:27,721 --> 01:31:30,181
Are you finished?

1166
01:31:36,353 --> 01:31:38,521
Valentin, would you
take me back, please?

1167
01:31:38,522 --> 01:31:40,817
Yes, of course.

1168
01:31:42,862 --> 01:31:46,780
Please, make way.
Make way. Make way.

1169
01:31:48,451 --> 01:31:52,578
I've behaved rather badly, haven't I?
No, countess.

1170
01:31:52,579 --> 01:31:54,830
No, don't worry.

1171
01:33:04,567 --> 01:33:08,154
Here. For you.

1172
01:33:14,869 --> 01:33:17,914
Is this clean?
Of course it's clean.

1173
01:33:20,960 --> 01:33:23,252
Dushan,
what's the matter?

1174
01:33:23,253 --> 01:33:25,462
Listen to him.

1175
01:33:25,463 --> 01:33:28,673
I'm supposed to be
a doctor, for God's sake.

1176
01:33:28,674 --> 01:33:31,009
Sofya?

1177
01:33:31,177 --> 01:33:32,970
Sofya?

1178
01:33:32,971 --> 01:33:35,263
What is it?

1179
01:33:35,598 --> 01:33:37,393
What is it?

1180
01:33:42,313 --> 01:33:45,274
She's come, hasn't she?

1181
01:33:45,775 --> 01:33:49,028
She's here.
You're imagining things.

1182
01:33:49,029 --> 01:33:50,737
Sasha!

1183
01:33:51,947 --> 01:33:54,201
Where is your mother?

1184
01:33:54,868 --> 01:33:57,286
She's at home.

1185
01:33:59,289 --> 01:34:02,833
If she wants to see me,
I can't refuse her.

1186
01:34:02,835 --> 01:34:04,960
Yes.

1187
01:34:05,337 --> 01:34:08,004
Is she going to come here?

1188
01:34:08,505 --> 01:34:10,634
I don't...

1189
01:34:10,926 --> 01:34:13,177
There's no way to...

1190
01:34:14,262 --> 01:34:17,306
There's no way to what?

1191
01:34:38,453 --> 01:34:41,121
I'd like to send
another telegram, please.

1192
01:34:42,375 --> 01:34:44,542
At Astapovo. Stop.

1193
01:34:45,877 --> 01:34:48,503
Tolstoy ill. Stop.

1194
01:34:48,504 --> 01:34:51,298
Heartbreaking. Stop.
Please come.

1195
01:34:53,344 --> 01:34:55,804
You can send it to Masha...

1196
01:34:56,137 --> 01:34:58,347
Maria Filipovna Melinova.

1197
01:35:02,310 --> 01:35:04,520
You lied to him.

1198
01:35:04,521 --> 01:35:06,145
Keep your voice down.

1199
01:35:06,146 --> 01:35:08,567
He wants to see her.
You heard him say it.

1200
01:35:08,942 --> 01:35:11,235
And what exactly do you
think she'll bring him here?

1201
01:35:11,237 --> 01:35:13,737
I don't know. They've been
married for 48 years.

1202
01:35:13,737 --> 01:35:16,574
I'll tell you exactly what she'll bring.
Vanity, fuss and noise.

1203
01:35:16,576 --> 01:35:17,992
She promised me
she would not...

1204
01:35:17,993 --> 01:35:20,077
Promised you what?
What, what?

1205
01:35:20,078 --> 01:35:22,162
You've seen her at
close quarters, my boy.

1206
01:35:22,163 --> 01:35:25,666
Do you really think that she's
capable of restraining herself
from acting like a madwoman?

1207
01:35:25,667 --> 01:35:27,918
They have a whole life together.
Why do you have to deny that?

1208
01:35:27,920 --> 01:35:30,922
You have become a victim
of her romantic nonsense.

1209
01:35:31,298 --> 01:35:34,842
And you willfully forget that she wants
to destroy everything we do.

1210
01:35:34,844 --> 01:35:37,094
She travels here with that
unctuous little priest.

1211
01:35:37,094 --> 01:35:40,722
We'll keep the priest away.
These people are vultures, Valentin.

1212
01:35:40,723 --> 01:35:43,350
And they wait to descend
till the very last moment

1213
01:35:43,351 --> 01:35:45,310
to welcome him back
to the Church.

1214
01:35:45,311 --> 01:35:47,645
This is their fantasy.
Keep the priest away.

1215
01:35:47,646 --> 01:35:49,189
A deathbed recantation.

1216
01:35:49,190 --> 01:35:53,819
Do you have any idea
the damage that that will do?

1217
01:35:53,820 --> 01:35:55,738
Everything that he has
dreamed of,

1218
01:35:55,739 --> 01:36:01,869
everything that we have
worked for will be gone.

1219
01:36:01,911 --> 01:36:05,247
A simple, noble death

1220
01:36:05,248 --> 01:36:07,875
is what we want.

1221
01:36:08,125 --> 01:36:10,795
That's what he wants.

1222
01:36:13,130 --> 01:36:16,134
No, you want
to create an icon.

1223
01:36:16,219 --> 01:36:19,677
And you want people
to kneel in front of an
image that you create.

1224
01:36:19,679 --> 01:36:21,305
But he doesn't want that.

1225
01:36:21,306 --> 01:36:25,183
He never has wanted that.
It'll give him no peace.

1226
01:36:26,645 --> 01:36:30,063
He wants to see her.
Let her come.

1227
01:36:31,692 --> 01:36:35,612
I will do everything in
my power to prevent that.

1228
01:36:37,905 --> 01:36:40,074
That image
you want to create,

1229
01:36:41,536 --> 01:36:44,411
it's going to look
more like you than him.

1230
01:37:47,808 --> 01:37:49,936
Valentin?

1231
01:38:06,911 --> 01:38:09,495
It can't be right.
His fever is down.

1232
01:38:09,496 --> 01:38:11,164
Yes.

1233
01:38:11,165 --> 01:38:13,000
But, uh...

1234
01:38:13,125 --> 01:38:17,504
his pulse,
you see, it's...

1235
01:38:24,762 --> 01:38:26,931
My dear.

1236
01:38:31,186 --> 01:38:33,770
Shall I call her?

1237
01:38:33,771 --> 01:38:36,524
He wouldn't know
who she is anyway.

1238
01:38:36,525 --> 01:38:38,359
Yes.

1239
01:39:02,842 --> 01:39:05,594
Bring a coat. It's cold.

1240
01:39:14,478 --> 01:39:18,399
Countess. Countess, could you
give me some information?

1241
01:39:18,400 --> 01:39:20,817
Countess, is he dying?

1242
01:39:20,987 --> 01:39:22,904
Is he dead?

1243
01:39:33,748 --> 01:39:38,002
Leovochka!
Leovochka, my darling.

1244
01:39:38,003 --> 01:39:40,754
Oh, my darling,
please forgive me, please!

1245
01:39:40,880 --> 01:39:45,885
I'm a fool. I'm a selfish woman,
but I love you, darling.

1246
01:39:45,886 --> 01:39:48,386
Please believe me.

1247
01:39:48,387 --> 01:39:52,016
Please, please understand me,

1248
01:39:52,018 --> 01:39:55,019
and please forgive my
wickedness and my badness.

1249
01:39:55,020 --> 01:39:57,312
Mother.

1250
01:39:57,688 --> 01:39:59,856
Control yourself.

1251
01:39:59,857 --> 01:40:03,737
Am I shouting?
You have to control yourself.

1252
01:40:06,239 --> 01:40:08,073
Yes.

1253
01:40:08,074 --> 01:40:10,536
Yes, I will.

1254
01:40:25,967 --> 01:40:30,387
You don't speak, but I hear you.

1255
01:40:31,388 --> 01:40:34,518
Do you love me, Leovochka?

1256
01:40:39,813 --> 01:40:43,192
I never stopped,
my little bird.

1257
01:40:46,154 --> 01:40:48,990
And you will never stop?

1258
01:40:50,451 --> 01:40:52,284
No.

1259
01:40:52,286 --> 01:40:54,328
Never.

1260
01:40:56,748 --> 01:40:59,292
Nor ever leave me again?

1261
01:41:01,835 --> 01:41:06,214
No, never again.

1262
01:41:06,591 --> 01:41:08,551
Good.

1263
01:41:08,802 --> 01:41:10,762
Good.

1264
01:41:12,097 --> 01:41:13,597
Let's go home.

1265
01:41:49,092 --> 01:41:51,552
First cessation.

1266
01:42:03,315 --> 01:42:05,982
Second cessation.

1267
01:42:24,170 --> 01:42:27,338
Shh. Shh.

1268
01:42:55,451 --> 01:43:00,329
Ten minutes after 6
in the morning,

1269
01:43:01,664 --> 01:43:04,750
a great soul passed
from our world.

1270
01:43:06,170 --> 01:43:09,880
Lev Nikolayevich Tolstoy...

1271
01:44:06,228 --> 01:44:08,313
Masha.

1272
01:44:15,280 --> 01:44:19,283
Masha. Oh, Masha.

1273
01:44:20,911 --> 01:44:24,204
I'm sorry, but he is gone.
I know.

1274
01:44:27,417 --> 01:44:30,460
But I came for you, Valya.

1275
01:44:31,545 --> 01:44:33,463
I came for you too.

1276
01:45:22,931 --> 01:45:25,599
God go with you,
Sofya Andreyevna.

1277
01:45:25,600 --> 01:45:28,061
God bless you!

1278
01:45:29,896 --> 01:45:33,067
We'll pray for you, countess!

